Full Description: The ski industry has always sought to bring the people to the mountain. It is their intention at steve little's ski/board enterprises / mt urban ski/board sports complex to take a $2 billion a year skiing industry with only a 3 - 31/2 month season, limited to fixed ski locations and snow conditions, around the country and the world and make it accessable year around in any location regardless of conditions. They intend to accomplish this through their state of the art mobile and fixed location ski/board camps which will be brought to any location in the u.S., canada, and the world, and there is no worry about bad or no snow conditions because they: "require no snow". They teach the art of free style ski/boarding to all participants, regardless of skill level; teach freestyle recreational ski/boarding - give lessons on virtual ski machines - train first time ski/boarders to reduce discouragement when on the resort slopes their first visit without basic skills, train the kids so the annual winter ski trip to their favorite ski resort will allow mom and dad free time on the big slopes instead of babysitting on the bunny slopes with the kids. They will accomplish this through excellence in service, innovation, and anticipation of their guest ever changing needs and expectations. There is currently no compition in the mobile ski/board industry and there are only 3-4 fixed location in the u.S. And most of them are located at the ski resorts leaving the rest of the u.S. An untaped market. They propost to meet and exceed that market need with their state of the art mobile and fixed location recreational ski/board camps. They have already tested the market with presentations of their concept and have received overwhelming positive response and have many facilities already asking us to come to their locations and hold camps for weeks at a time. To equip each mobil and/or fixed location ski/board camp requires $750,000 initial investment. They are projecting as much as 25-50% return on investment.

Description: Innovating coastal livelihoods that drive marine ecosystem restoration
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Olazul is a nonprofit organization dedicated to developing sustainable livelihoods in balance with healthy ecosystems through the principles of ecological aquaculture. The ecological aquaculture is a framework that mixes the scientific knowledge of aquatic ecosystems experts with the social-ecological knowledge of the coastal communities engaged in aquaculture. This results in economic, environmental, and social benefits from producing seafood in a way that is good for humanity and our oceans. This framework helps businesses produce high-quality seafood, and become more economically stable. It also encourages high-quality research on fisheries, supports innovative solutions driving change in the aquaculture sector, and provides a way for communities to continue applying and deepening their knowledge of local ecosystems.  The model behind Olazul resembles that of an incubator in that it helps develop skills and create economic opportunities for fishermen to ensure the long-term sustainability of their ocean-based livelihoods. The organization runs projects around the world but each targets the most destructive activities and creates alternative production systems through aquaculture. For instance, one project is in the sustainable livelihood development of ornamental fish in Indonesia. Rather than destroying corals with cyanide fishing, coastal communities protect them as a way to grow fish for the aquarium trade. This project will reinforce ecological conservation and provide employment opportunities for both men and women
